						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara; Sāvaṇṇa oḍeya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1284 <hi rend="bold">Sōbhakṛit, Māgha śu.</hi> which falls in the Śaka year 1284 corresponding to 1362 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. It seems to record the construction of a temple by Ippasāni and grants made to it. The name of the donor is lost. It mentions Sāvōṇnōḍayalu.</p>						

						</summary>
